ense offshore casinos, player protection depends on the overseas regulator. \n        That\u2019s why checking a site\u2019s <strong>licence, payout history and terms</strong> is far more important \n        than just the size of the welcome bonus. For a full legal and safety overview, see our \n        <a href=\"/new-zealand-safety-legal-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n          New Zealand Safety &amp; Legal Guide\n        </a>.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q2 -->\n    <div class=\"tcs-faq-card\"\n         style=\"border-radius:16px; padding:18px 18px 20px; background:rgba(10,12,38,0.9); border:1px solid #313766;\">\n      <h3 style=\"font-size:1.02rem; margin-bottom:6px;\">What are the safest payment methods for New Zealand players?</h3>\n      <p><strong>Short answer:</strong> NZD bank transfer, POLi/instant banking, debit/credit cards, e-wallets and, at some sites, crypto.</p>\n      <p>\n        Most NZ-facing casinos support <strong>Visa and Mastercard</strong> (debit and often credit), \n        NZD <strong>bank transfers</strong>, <strong>POLi or other instant banking options</strong>, and \n        international e-wallets such as <strong>Skrill, Neteller or ecoPayz</strong>.  \n        Some offshore brands also accept crypto (BTC, USDT, ETH, etc.) alongside NZD methods.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n        Safer casinos clearly show processing times, limits and any fees before you confirm a transaction.  \n        Treat requests to send money to a personal bank or crypto wallet outside the cashier as a major red flag.  \n        We compare the most reliable options in our \n        <a href=\"/new-zealand-banking-guide/\">\n          New Zealand Casino Banking &amp; Fast-Payout Guide\n        </a>.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q3 -->\n    <div class=\"tcs-faq-card\"\n         style=\"border-radius:16px; padding:18px 18px 20px; background:rgba(10,12,38,0.9); border:1px solid #313766;\">\n      <h3 style=\"font-size:1.02rem; margin-bott